<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The Caring Place is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone, and applying the relevant accessibility standards.</p>

      <h2>Our commitment</h2>
      <p>We believe access to information and services is a collective moral obligation — allowing seamless, accessible, and unhindered use of our site for those of us with disabilities is core to who we are. We've invested resources to help ensure our website is easier to use and more accessible for people with disabilities.</p>

      <h2>Ongoing efforts</h2>
      <p>We aim to align with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1. Some content may not yet be fully adapted to the strictest accessibility standards — this may be due to not having found or implemented the most appropriate technological solution yet. We're actively working to improve this over time.</p>

      <h2>Feedback</h2>
      <p>If you experience any difficulty accessing any part of this website, please let us know:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:jessical@thecaringplacenwi.org">jessical@thecaringplacenwi.org</a></li>
        <li>24-Hour Crisis Line: <a href="tel:219-464-2128">219-464-2128</a> or <a href="tel:1-800-933-0466">1-800-933-0466</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
